subModels.name: Import OSDU Schema
subModels.description:
# OSDU Schema
This Template startmodel is set up with Object Types necessary for importing OSDU Type Definitions. 
These Type Definitions are stored as JSON-files 
and we can download these files and import them into AKMM as Typedefinition Models.


You can find the Schema here:
[OSDU Schema](https://community.opengroup.org/osdu/data/data-definitions/-/tree/master/Generated)

objects.name: Download json file(s)
objects.description:
#### Download Schema from OSDU

OSDU Schema is stored as JSON-files in: 
[https://community.opengroup.org/osdu/data/data-definitions/Generated](https://community.opengroup.org/osdu/data/data-definitions/-/tree/master/Generated)

Cick on the Downlad-button ( upper-right ) and you can download the whole directory.
Unpack the zip-file, and you now have a folder with all OSDU Schema- types

objects.name: Import json file(s)
objects.description:
### Import Schema files into AKM Modeller

Click on the OSDU (blue button) in the Modelling bar.

Click "Choose files" and locate the folder where you downloaded the OSDU json-files.

Select one or more files to be imported.

Click on the blue  "Done" button at the down-right.
Click on the "Reload" button in the Modelling bar.

Open the "Objects" pane to the left (next to the modeling area)

Drag and drop the Schema-types (white objects) into the modelling area.

Click on the "OSDU" button in the Modeling bar again.

Click on "GENERATE RELATIONSHIPS BETWEEN ENTITYTYPES (PROPERTYLINKS)" to generate relationship between the types.

Right-Click on the background and select: "Add Missing Relationship Views"

Arrange the objects (You can make Containers to organize the Objects)

objects.name: View the Properties
objects.description:
### View the Propertes of the Type (EntityType)

First make a new Modelview (You can name it "2-Properties")

Copy one or more of the EntityTypes.

Open the new Modelview and "Paste as view"
Arrange the objectviews with some distance.

Right-click one of them and select "Add Connected Objects"

Keep the sublevels = 1
(this will add the properties of the EntityType)
